  • John Heutmekers
    5star
    Mon Français n'est pas très bon, alors je continue en Anglais.
    Paris is a wonderful city, we have been here several time...s. So much to see and visit, you can have a drink at almost every corner of the city and numerous restaurants to enjoy both lunch and dinner. There is always a metro station nearby, which makes visiting this huge city enjoyable. However during our last trip we had a very bad experience when travelling with the metro. Before we came to Paris we bought a Paris visite card for travelling with the metro. On our third day an officer of the metro wanted our tickets for what we thought was a check. He wanted to make us pay a fine of 33 euros because we didn't fill in our names on the tickets. We had a long discussion with him (because our French isn't that good and he didn't speak any other language.....). We told him that it would be ridiculously to pay a fine for a valid ticket only because we didn't put our name on the ticket. He refused to listen to our arguments and only after we told him to call the police he was willing to just give us a warning. Both the fact that an officer doesn't speak any other language then French and the fact he wanted to make us pay a fine for a valid ticket ruined this day. See More
    March 12, 2016 ·
